\alias{SeqDesignInferenceAbstractKKIncidRandCI}
\title{Abstract class for randomisation-based CI for incidence outcomes}
\description{
Provides \code{compute_confidence_interval_rand()} for binary (incidence)
responses under CRD (\code{SeqDesignCRD}) or KK matching-on-the-fly
(\code{SeqDesignKK14} and subclasses) designs.  All other design types are
rejected with an error.

Binary responses cannot be shifted by an additive \eqn{\delta_0}, so the
standard continuous-outcome trick is unavailable.  Instead, the CI is
obtained by test-inversion: for each candidate \eqn{\delta_0}, a combined
two-sided p-value is computed from the matched-pair component (zero for CRD)
and the Bernoulli-randomised reservoir component via Fisher's independence
method.  The boundaries of
\eqn{\{\delta_0 : p_\text{combined}(\delta_0) > \alpha\}}
are located by bisection.

\strong{Estimation (point estimate, MLE CI, MLE p-value)} is the same
compound clogit + logistic estimator as \code{SeqDesignInferenceAbstractKKClogit}:
conditional logistic regression on matched pairs (requires \pkg{bclogit}
when \eqn{m > 0}) combined with standard logistic regression on the
reservoir, variance-weighted.  For CRD designs (\eqn{m = 0}) the estimator
reduces to pure logistic regression and \pkg{bclogit} is not needed.

\strong{Subclasses} must implement two private methods:
\itemize{
  \item \code{compute_rand_pval_matched_pairs(delta_0)}: two-sided p-value
        for \eqn{H_0 : \mathrm{ATE}_\mathrm{pairs} = \delta_0}.  Return
        \code{NA_real_} when there are no matched pairs or no discordant
        pairs.
  \item \code{compute_rand_pval_reservoir(delta_0)}: two-sided p-value for
        \eqn{H_0 : \mathrm{ATE}_\mathrm{reservoir} = \delta_0}.  Return
        \code{NA_real_} when either reservoir arm is empty.
}
Subclasses may also override \code{include_covariates()} (default
\code{FALSE}) and \code{combine_rand_pvals()} to change the combination
rule.
}
